<p><b>Human Rights Council 
Twenty-seventh session 
</b></p>
<p>Agenda item 3 
</p>
<p><b>Promotion and protection of all human rights, civil, 
</b></p>
<p><b>political, economic, social and cultural rights, 
</b></p>
<p><b>including the right to development 
</b></p>
<p><b>  Bahrain,</b><footnote name="*">Non-member State of the Human Rights Council.  </footnote><b> China, Cuba, Egypt,</b><footnote name="*">Non-member State of the Human Rights Council.  </footnote><b> Russian Federation, United Arab Emirates, 
</b></p>
<p><b>Venezuela (Bolivarian Republic of): amendment to draft resolution A/HRC/27/L.24 
</b></p>
<p><b>  27</b>/&#8230;  <b>Civil society space 
</b></p>
<p>The eleventh preambular paragraph <i>should read</i> 
</p>
<p><i>Deeply concerned</i> that, in some instances, domestic legal and administrative 
</p>
<p>provisions, such as national security and counter-terrorism legislation, and other measures, 
</p>
<p>such as provisions on funding to civil society actors, hinder the work and endanger the 
</p>
<p>safety of civil society in a manner contrary to international law, and recognizing the urgent 
</p>
<p>need to prevent and stop the use of such provisions, and to review and, where necessary, 
</p>
<p>amend any relevant provisions in order to ensure their compliance with relevant domestic 
</p>
<p>laws consistent with the State&#8217;s international human rights law obligations and, as 
</p>
<p>appropriate, international humanitarian law, 
</p>
<p>    
